Class Project

java.lang.Object
BTOManagementSystem.Model.Project
public class Project extends Object
Represents a Build-To-Order (BTO) project within the HDB system.

Each project includes attributes like name, location (neighbourhood), available flat types with units and prices, application window, manager in charge, officer slots, assigned officers, and visibility status.

      public Project(String name, String Neighbourhood, String type1, int Type1_numofunits, double Type1_sellingprice, String Type2, int Type2_numofunits, double type2_selling_price, String openingDate, String closingDate, String manager, int officerslots, String officers, int visibility)
      Constructs a new Project with all required details.
      Parameters:
      name - the project name
      Neighbourhood - the location of the project
      type1 - the first flat type (e.g., 2-Room)
      Type1_numofunits - number of units for type1
      Type1_sellingprice - selling price for type1
      Type2 - the second flat type (e.g., 3-Room)
      Type2_numofunits - number of units for type2
      type2_selling_price - selling price for type2
      openingDate - application opening date (format: dd-MM-yyyy)
      closingDate - application closing date (format: dd-MM-yyyy)
      manager - manager's name
      officerslots - available officer slots
      officers - comma-separated list of officer names
      visibility - 1 = visible, 0 = hidden
